      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of September 28 Design Notebook column on pictograms and other icons</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Design Notebook column last Thursday, about annoyance over cryptic Olympic pictograms and other icons, misstated the meaning of a red traffic light in China. It means stop. During the Cultural Revolution 30 years ago, an effort was made to change the meaning to ''go,'' but the idea did not take hold.</p>
      </block>
